
Base URL for the Parity backend API
API_BASE_URL=https://api.example.com

Firebase Project Configuration
These values can be found in your Firebase project settings
FIREBASE_API_KEY=your_firebase_api_key FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=your_project_id.firebaseapp.com FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=your_project_id FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=your_project_id.appspot.com FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=your_sender_id FIREBASE_APP_ID=your_app_id FIREBASE_MEASUREMENT_ID=your_measurement_id

Google Sign-In Configuration
This is the Web Client ID from your Google Cloud Platform credentials
GOOGLE_SIGNIN_WEB_CLIENT_ID=your_google_web_client_id.apps.googleusercontent.com

Secret key for local client-side encryption.
WARNING: For production, this should be managed securely (e.g., fetched from a secure keychain)
and not hardcoded or stored in plaintext. This is a placeholder for development.
ENCRYPTION_SECRET_KEY=a_very_strong_and_long_secret_for_local_encryption